@startuml flujo-k6-crud
!theme plain
title Diagrama de Flujo - realistic-crud-flow.js (k6)\nFlujo CRUD completo por iteracion de VU

skinparam activity {
  BackgroundColor #D5F5E3
  BorderColor #27AE60
  DiamondBackgroundColor #FEF9E7
  DiamondBorderColor #F39C12
}
skinparam backgroundColor #FAFAFA

start

note
  Ejecutado por cada VU (Virtual User)
  en paralelo durante DURATION (ej: 60s)
  Cada iteracion es un ciclo CRUD completo
end note

:Inicio de iteracion (VU #N, iter #M);

:login()\nPOST AUTH_BASE/login\n(username:"demo", password:"demo123");

if (status 200 AND has access_token?) then (Si)
  :loginOk.add(1)\ntoken = access_token;
else (No)
  :loginFail.add(1) | token = null;
  :sleep(1s) - Early return: no hay token;
  detach
endif

:listProducts(token)\nGET API_BASE/products?limit=20&offset=0\nAuthorization: Bearer token;

:listLatency.add(duration)\ncheck: status 200 | listOk o listFail++;

:createProduct(token, VU, ITER)\nPOST API_BASE/products\n(name:"k6-prod-vuN-itM-TS", price:random);

if (status 200 AND data.id presente?) then (Si)
  :createOk.add(1)\nid = data.id | createLatency.add(duration);
else (No)
  :createFail.add(1) | id = null;
  :sleep(0.3s) - Sin id: saltar read/update/delete;
  detach
endif

:readProduct(token, id)\nGET API_BASE/products/:id\nAuthorization: Bearer token;

:readLatency.add(duration)\ncheck: status 200 | readOk o readFail++;

:updateProduct(token, id)\nPUT API_BASE/products/:id\n(name:"k6-prod-id-upd", price:99.99);

:updateLatency.add(duration)\ncheck: status 200 | updateOk o updateFail++;

:readProduct(token, id) - Segunda lectura post-update\nGET API_BASE/products/:id;

:readLatency.add(duration) x2\nreadOk o readFail++;

:deleteProduct(token, id)\nDELETE API_BASE/products/:id;

if (status 200 OR 204?) then (Si)
  :deleteOk.add(1);
else (No)
  :deleteFail.add(1);
endif

note right : Si delete falla el producto queda en DB.\nAcumulacion posible bajo alta carga.

:deleteLatency.add(duration);

:sleep(0.3s) - pacing entre iteraciones;

note right
  Requests por iteracion: 7
  login + list + create +
  read + update + read + delete
end note

:Fin de iteracion - siguiente si aun hay tiempo;

stop

note bottom
  Thresholds (criterio pass/fail):
  - http_req_failed: rate < 5%
  - http_req_duration: p95 < 700ms
  - checks: rate > 95%
  - crud_create/read/update/delete_success_total: count > 0
  Metricas: Counter ok/fail + Trend latency_ms por operacion
end note
@enduml
